Ronald Spiers, a veteran US diplomat will be the new undersecretary-general for General Assembly affairs at the UN.
Secretary-General Javier Perez de Cuellar announced the appointment.
This is the top ranking American post at the world body and Spiers will replace Joseph Reed, a banker who served in that post until since 1983.
Reed will become chief of protocol for the United States.
Spiers is a career foreign service officer and has been ambassador to the Bahamas and Turkey and, from 1981 until 1983 was ambassador to Pakistan.
Spiers most recent job was undersecretary of state for management affairs. 
